- NumPy — BSD-3-Clause — https://github.com/numpy/numpy

Bundled fonts (fonts/ directory)
--------------------------------
Metric-compatible substitute fonts, each under the SIL Open Font License 1.1
or Apache License 2.0 — see fonts/licenses/ for the license text shipped with
each family:
- Carlito (Google) — OFL-1.1 — metric-compatible with Calibri
- Caladea (Huerta Tipográfica) — OFL-1.1 — metric-compatible with Cambria
- Arimo, Tinos, Cousine (Steve Matteson / Monotype) — metric-compatible with
  Arial, Times New Roman, Courier New
- Noto Sans, Noto Sans Devanagari (Google) — OFL-1.1

The OFL permits bundling, web serving, and embedding these fonts (or subsets)
in generated documents; it forbids selling the fonts standalone. License
notices are preserved in fonts/licenses/.

